Tenant Dashboard / Tenant Functionalities
Tenants have access to their own electronic dashboard in the system where they can:

1. View Personal and Payment Information
   - View their tenant record, including:
     - Payment history (list of all payments made and due)
     - Lease agreement details
     - Apartment details (assigned unit, type, location)
   - View graphical representations of:
     - Payment history over time
     - Tenant payments compared to neighbors
     - Late payments per property

2. Payments and Billing
   - Receive alerts for late payments automatically.
   - Make payments through the dashboard:
     - System validates card info (simulated)
     - Creates a record of the “payment” in the system
   - View pending dues or unpaid balances

3. Complaints and Maintenance Requests
   - Submit a complaint via the dashboard.
   - Submit a repair/maintenance request.
   - View the progress/status of repair requests:
     - Whether maintenance is scheduled
     - Updates on completion
     - Time taken and costs recorded by maintenance staff (optional for info)

4. Early Lease Termination
   - Request to leave before the end of contract:
     - Must provide 1-month notice
     - System calculates penalty of 5% of monthly rent


